        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hosted Web Search"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic's hosted web search tool lets Claude retrieve live information from the internet without you building a search integration or running a tool loop. You declare the tool in the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tools"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list; Claude decides when to search, issues the query internally, and incorporates the results into its final answer \u2014 all in a single API call from your perspective."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Hosted web search flow diagram showing Claude API calling search internally",
          "title": "Hosted Web Search Flow"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Hosted web search is available on "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and newer models. It requires enabling the tool in your request \u2014 it is not active by default. Verify current model support in the Anthropic documentation."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Enabling Web Search"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pass a tool definition with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "type: 'web_search_20250305'"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tools"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list. No additional configuration is required \u2014 Anthropic manages the search backend."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    tools=[\n        {\n            \"type\": \"web_search_20250305\",\n            \"name\": \"web_search\"\n        }\n    ],\n    messages=[\n        {\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": \"What were the main announcements at Google I/O 2025?\"\n        }\n    ]\n)\n\n# The response is already the final answer \u2014 no tool loop needed\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reading Citations from the Response"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Claude uses web search, the response content may include "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "web_search_result_location"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks alongside text blocks. These carry the URL and title of each page that Claude cited. Iterate the full content list to extract both the answer text and its sources."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"web_search_20250305\", \"name\": \"web_search\"}],\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is the current Python stable release version?\"}]\n)\n\nanswer_parts = []\ncitations = []\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        answer_parts.append(block.text)\n    elif block.type == \"web_search_result_location\":\n        citations.append({\n            \"url\":   block.url,\n            \"title\": getattr(block, \"title\", \"\"),\n        })\n\nprint(\"Answer:\")\nprint(\"\".join(answer_parts))\nprint()\nprint(\"Sources:\")\nfor i, c in enumerate(citations, 1):\n    print(f\"  [{i}] {c['title']} \u2014 {c['url']}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining Web Search with Custom Tools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can mix the hosted web search tool with your own custom tools in the same request. Claude will decide which tool to invoke based on the query. Custom tools still require a tool loop; web search results are injected automatically before the final response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, json\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nTOOLS = [\n    # Hosted web search \u2014 Anthropic manages execution\n    {\"type\": \"web_search_20250305\", \"name\": \"web_search\"},\n    # Custom tool \u2014 you execute this yourself\n    {\n        \"name\": \"get_exchange_rate\",\n        \"description\": \"Return the current exchange rate between two currencies.\",\n        \"input_schema\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n                \"from_currency\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"e.g. USD\"},\n                \"to_currency\":   {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"e.g. EUR\"}\n            },\n            \"required\": [\"from_currency\", \"to_currency\"]\n        }\n    }\n]\n\ndef get_exchange_rate(from_currency: str, to_currency: str) -> dict:\n    rates = {(\"USD\", \"EUR\"): 0.92, (\"USD\", \"GBP\"): 0.79}\n    rate = rates.get((from_currency, to_currency))\n    if rate:\n        return {\"from\": from_currency, \"to\": to_currency, \"rate\": rate}\n    return {\"error\": f\"Unknown pair: {from_currency}/{to_currency}\"}\n\nmessages = [\n    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What's the USD to EUR rate, and what's the latest news about the Euro?\"}\n]\n\nwhile True:\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        tools=TOOLS,\n        messages=messages\n    )\n    messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n\n    if response.stop_reason == \"end_turn\":\n        for block in response.content:\n            if block.type == \"text\":\n                print(block.text)\n        break\n\n    # Only custom tools need manual execution \u2014 web_search is handled internally\n    tool_results = []\n    for block in response.content:\n        if block.type == \"tool_use\" and block.name == \"get_exchange_rate\":\n            result = get_exchange_rate(**block.input)\n            tool_results.append({\n                \"type\":        \"tool_result\",\n                \"tool_use_id\": block.id,\n                \"content\":     json.dumps(result)\n            })\n\n    if tool_results:\n        messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n    else:\n        break\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Controlling Search Behaviour"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can guide when Claude uses web search through your system prompt. Setting a clear retrieval policy reduces unnecessary search calls and cuts token costs."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nSYSTEM = \"\"\"You are a research assistant.\nUse web search ONLY when the user explicitly asks for current or real-time information,\nor when the question cannot be answered from your training data.\nFor general knowledge questions, answer directly without searching.\"\"\"\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    system=SYSTEM,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"web_search_20250305\", \"name\": \"web_search\"}],\n    messages=[\n        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"What is the capital of France?\"}\n        # Claude should answer from knowledge, not search\n    ]\n)\n\n# Check whether a search was actually performed\nsearched = any(\n    getattr(b, \"type\", \"\") == \"tool_use\" and getattr(b, \"name\", \"\") == \"web_search\"\n    for b in response.content\n)\nprint(f\"Search used: {searched}\")\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming with Web Search"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming works normally when web search is enabled. The search happens server-side; you receive text deltas once Claude begins composing its answer. Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "stream.text_stream"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for simple streaming or "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "get_final_message()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to retrieve the full response with citations."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nwith client.messages.stream(\n    model=\"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n    max_tokens=1024,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"web_search_20250305\", \"name\": \"web_search\"}],\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Summarise the latest news about open-source AI models.\"}]\n) as stream:\n    for text in stream.text_stream:\n        print(text, end=\"\", flush=True)\n    print()\n\n    # Retrieve citations from the complete message\n    final = stream.get_final_message()\n    citations = [\n        b for b in final.content\n        if getattr(b, \"type\", \"\") == \"web_search_result_location\"\n    ]\n    if citations:\n        print(\"\\nSources:\")\n        for c in citations:\n            print(f\"  {c.url}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
